  "title": "ID & Archi Coordination (Intern/ Part Time)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>·       Assist in reviewing and coordinating\narchitectural and interior design (ID) drawings to ensure consistency with the\ndesign intent and site conditions.</p><p>·       Support the compilation,\norganization, and tracking of design-related documents, drawings, and\nmaterials.</p><p>·       Contribute to the preparation of\ndesign presentations, material boards, and meeting minutes.</p><p>·       Coordinate with consultants,\nsubcontractors, and suppliers to address design clarifications and updates.</p><p>·       Assist the architectural team in\nfollowing up on technical submissions, responses, and closures.</p><p>·       Support the team in monitoring site\nprogress related to design implementation.</p><p>·       Perform other administrative and\ncoordination tasks as assigned by the Design Team.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>·       \nCurrently pursuing a <strong>Diploma or Degree\nin Architecture, Interior Design, or related discipline</strong>.</p><p>·       \nProficient in <strong>AutoCAD, SketchUp, and\nMicrosoft Office</strong> (Revit or Photoshop is a plus).</p>",
